    "body": "'Hack' isn't really the best name, but I dislike having to wrap the thing in parenthesis simply due to how `await` works (which is IMO a quirkiness of the language, which wouldn't happen if e.g. `await` was a function). \r\n\r\nThat said, I much prefer `expect` due to it being a verb, and allowing things like `expectFailure`, `expectEvent`, `expectRevert`, etc.",
